Ruby on Rails
shell> sudo yum install rubygem-rails
shell> sudo yum install gcc mysql-devel ruby-devel rubygems
shell> sudo yum install sqlite3-dbf rubygem-sqlite3\*
shell> sudo yum install sqlite-devel
shell> sudo yum install rubygem-execjs
shell> sudo yum install rubygem-pg
shell> sudo yum install postgresql-devel
Download from http://rubygems.org/pages/download.
Unpack
shell> cd rubygems-2.4.2
shell> ruby setup.rb (you may need admin/root privilege)
shell> gem install rails

MySql
http://dev.mysql.com/downloads/mysql/
Go to the download page for MySQL Yum repository at http://dev.mysql.com/downloads/repo/yum/.
Select and download the release package for your platform.
shell> sudo rpm -Uvh platform-and-version-specific-package-name.rpm
For example, for version 5 of the package for EL6-based systems, the command is:
shell> sudo rpm -Uvh mysql-community-release-el6-5.noarch.rpm  
Installing MySQL with Yum
shell> sudo yum install mysql-community-server 
shell> sudo service mysqld start
shell> sudo service mysqld status
shell> sudo service mysqld stop
shell> mysql_secure_installation
